This directory hosts the code for the NVIDIA CSWP-Client.
See LICENSE.txt for license and Copyright informations

1- Origin:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The code is based on the public CSWP client implementation from ARM:
https://github.com/ARM-software/coresight-wire-protocol
using following steps:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. wget https://github.com/ARM-software/coresight-wire-protocol/archive/refs/heads/master.zip          // Get archive of latest version (07/30/2024) of repo
2. sha256sum master.zip                                                                                // 712ec2cf2e83dd2527d7f3a3507ce24ebca757f23283ecb82fbe055457e9d28f
3. unzip master.zip                                                                                    // Extracts zip file to coresight-wire-protocol-master
4. mv coresight-wire-protocol-master coresight-wire-protocol                                           // Rename to remove master from the name
5. rm ./.gitignore ./cswp/.gitignore ./rddi_streaming_trace/.gitignore ./target/cswp_server/.gitignore // Remove .gitignore files

For a description of the CSWP protocol this software is based on see https://github.com/ARM-software/coresight-wire-protocol/blob/master/cswp/doc/CSWP%20Protocol%20Specification.pdf

2- Platforms
Building client for x86_64 Linux host only
Supported OS: Ubuntu 18.04+, CentOS 7 and BMC.

3- CCU
This is a tool written by Nvidia and distributed along with the CSWP client
library. It is a command line utility tool that you can run to test the CSWP
client or run some basic commands.

4- Build
You need cmake version 3.31.3
mkdir build
cd build
cmake .. -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=<install_path>
make -j8 install
